name: Aai Caretaker
briefDescription: AAI is a Marathi word. Which means “Mother” and Caretaker means a “Guardian” A word that capture a Mother Spirit who take care of entire universe. AAI Caretaker is a Non – Government Organization registered under the Societies Registration Act 1860 & Bombay Public Trust Act 1950. Whose mandate is to protect and promote Environment, Health & Education. It was established in 2009 and located at Chembur, Mumbai.
